Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 09 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'MUscles' from the dropdown menu

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled

And 'Fatty degeneration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscular hypotrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscle atrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Apophysitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fascial laceration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Reduced ischiofemoral space' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Hematoma' checkbox
Then 'Intramuscular' checkbox is enabled
And 'Interfacial' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intermuscular' checkbox is enabled

And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled

And 'Hyperacute' radio button is enabled
And 'Acute' radio button is enabled
And 'Subacute' radio button is enabled
And 'Chronic, organized' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Muscle atrophy' checkbox
Then 'Complete' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Fascial laceration' checkbox
Then 'Muscle herniation' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Reduced ischiofemoral space' checkbox
Then 'Shortest distance' input field is enabled
